alert.note: Alert for Central Coast; North Coast (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Warning issued December 27 at 3:44AM PST until December 27 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 10 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...HIGH SURF WARNING IS CANCELLED... * WHAT...Significant coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast zones. * WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 10 PM PST this evening. * IMPACTS...Numerous roads may be closed. Low lying property including homes, businesses, and some critical infrastructure will be inundated. Some shoreline erosion will occur. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...High tide anomalies of 1 to 2 feet expected. After high tide later today swells building to 25 to 27 feet. Swell will subside later tonight.
info.instruction: Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. If travel is required, do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth.
